<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-bs-theme="auto">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta name="description" content="A lightweight, open-source, privacy-focused file sharing tool.">
  <meta name="og:site_name" content="Dropgate | Privacy-first File Sharing">
  <meta name="og:title" content="<%= serverName %>">
  <meta name="og:description" content="A lightweight, open-source, privacy-focused file sharing tool.">
  <meta name="og:type" content="website">
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#57F287">
  <link rel="icon" href="/assets/favicon.ico" type="image/x-icon">
  <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/assets/favicon.ico" type="image/x-icon">
  <link rel="manifest" href="/manifest.json" />
  <title><%= serverName %></title>

  <link href="/vendor/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link href="/assets/material-icons-round.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/bootstrap-base.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/error.css" />

  <script src="/js/theme.js" defer></script>
  <script type="module" src="/js/page-common.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
  <main>
    <div class="container-main text-center">
      <div id="title-container" class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center">
        <img src="/assets/icon.png" alt="Dropgate Icon" width="34" height="34" class="me-2 align-middle"
          loading="lazy" style="display:block;">
        <h1 class="h3 fw-semibold mb-0" style="line-height:1;">Dropgate</h1>
      </div>
      <p class="lead mb-4">A lightweight, open-source, privacy-focused file sharing tool.</p>

      <div id="status-card" class="card shadow-sm border-danger">
        <div class="card-body p-4">
          <div id="icon-container" class="mb-3 text-danger">
            <span class="material-icons-round">https</span>
          </div>

          <h5 class="card-title mb-2" id="status-title">Secure Connection Required</h5>
          <p class="card-text text-body-secondary" id="status-message">
            End-to-end encrypted files can only be downloaded over a secure HTTPS connection.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="help-statement" class="text-body-secondary mt-4">
        <strong>Why am I seeing this page?</strong><br>
        <p>The uploader enabled End-to-End Encryption (E2EE) for this file.<br>This page decrypts the file directly in
          your browser using the key in the URL.<br>Nobody else, not even the server, can read the true contents of your
          file.</p>

        <p>Modern browsers only allow the JavaScript Web Crypto API (crypto.subtle) and related secure storage features
          in secure contexts.<br>Because this page is being served over unsecured HTTP, the browser blocks decryption
          and saving of the file.</p>

        <p>If you are the owner of this server, enable HTTPS/TLS (for example via Let's Encrypt or a properly configured
          reverse proxy). Once served over HTTPS the browser will permit the Web Crypto API to decrypt and save the
          file.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <%= serverName %> <span id="server-version"></span> |
        <a href="https://github.com/WillTDA/Dropgate" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View on GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </footer>
</body>

</html>